review_content:
Updated rating summer ’08.  I add a full point on for summer purposes.  Actually, compared to American macros, you really can tell the difference.  It’s light but it doesn’t have the plasticky corn intrusiveness.
&lt;P&gt;
Flimsy, flimsy, flimsy.   Intercourse in a boat.  Not much aroma, appearance, flavor or palate to speak of.  Only hint of distinctiveness is some slightly sour tinge, the kind that’s an unwelcome characteristic of many Euro imports.  (I’m wondering if this is even a genuine import.)  I had a regular Sam Adams right after this and it blew this out of the water, so to speak.  Wouldn’t pay money for this again.
